NONOPERATIVE
TREATMENT
OF
MECONIUM
ILEUS
EQUIVALENT
INTRALUMINAL
BOWEL
OBSTRUCTION
SECONDARY
TO
INSPISSATED
FECES
IS
A
KNOWN
COMPLICATION
OF
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
WHEN
SEEN
IN
THE
OLDER
CHILD
IT
IS
TERMED
MECONIUM
ILEUS
EQUIVALENT
WE
STUDIED
A
CASE
IN
WHICH
NONSURGICAL
RESOLUTION
OF
THE
OBSTRUCTION
WAS
OBTAINED
WITH
N
ACETYLCYSTEINE
ENEMAS
AND
PANCREATIC
REPLACEMENT
ENZYMES
GIVEN
ORALLY
AND
BY
ENEMA
THE
PATHOGENESIS
OF
THIS
DISORDER
AND
THE
BASIS
FOR
THE
TREATMENT
ARE
DESCRIBED
RECOGNITION
OF
THIS
COMPLICATION
AND
FAMILIARITY
WITH
ITS
MEDICAL
MANAGEMENT
ARE
IMPORTANT
IN
CARING
FOR
THE
OLDER
CHILD
WITH
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
